  <num>16-2347</num>
  <heading>Death of respondent; liability of estate.</heading>
  <text>If the respondent dies after parentage has been established and prior to the time the child reaches the age at which the child ceases to be a minor, any sums due and unpaid under an order of the court at the time of his or her death shall constitute a valid claim against his or her estate.</text>
